@page "/"

<PageTitle>CS 3500 Starter Code for Chatting Project</PageTitle>

<h1>Networking is Fun!</h1>

<p>Welcome to the CS 3500 Chatting Project.</p>

<hr />

<h2>How the Project is Organized</h2>
<ul>
    <li><strong>NetworkConnection</strong>: A small helper class that wraps a TcpClient, StreamReader, and StreamWriter so you can send and receive lines of text.</li>
    <li><strong>ServerConnection</strong>: A static helper that listens for incoming TCP connections on a given port and hands each new client to the handler method on its own thread.</li>
    <li><strong>ChatServer</strong>: Uses ServerConnection and NetworkConnection to accept clients, read their usernames, and broadcast messages to every connected client.</li>
    <li><strong>ChatClient (Blazor page)</strong>: The GUI client that lets you connect to the server, send messages, and see messages from all users.</li>
</ul>

<hr />

<h2>Running the Chat Server and Client</h2>
<ol>
    <li>In Visual Studio, set the solution to start multiple projects at once.</li>
    <li>Select both ChatServer and ChatClient as startup projects.</li>
    <li>Run the solution — the ChatServer console window will open first and begin listening for clients on port 11000.</li>
    <li>The Blazor ChatClient will open in your browser automatically and can clients now connect to the running ChatServer.</li>
    <li>You can open additional browser tabs or windows to start multiple clients, each connecting to the same server instance.</li>
</ol>

<hr />

<h2>Using the Chat Client</h2>
<ol>
    <li>After both projects are running, navigate to the Chat Client page in your browser.</li>
    <li>
        Enter:
        <ul>
            <li>Your display name ( this is how messages from clients will be tagged ).</li>
            <li>The server address ( in our case it is: localhost ).</li>
            <li>The server port ( default: 11000 ).</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Click Connect.</li>
    <li>
        Once connected:
        <ul>
            <li>Type your message into the chat box.</li>
            <li>Press Enter to send.</li>
            <li>Your message is sent to the server and broadcast to all connected clients.</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Click Disconnect to close your connection and stop sending or receiving messages.</li>
</ol>
